UserProvisioningLog.name: UserProvisioningLog
UserProvisioningLog.description: Represents messages generated during the process of provisioning users for third-party applications.

Details.description: The value of this field depends on the log entry. For example, if the target system returns an error, the error message may be recorded in this field.

ExternalUserId.description: The unique identifier for the user in the target system.

ExternalUsername.description: The username set in the target system for the associated user account.

Name.description: The unique name for this object.

OwnerId.description: Salesforce ID of the Group or User who owns this object.

Status.description: The status of the user provisioning request. Based on the context of the log, it can contain different values, such as an HttpStatusCode.

UserId.description: Salesforce ID of the user making the request.

UserProvisioningRequestId.description: A unique identifier for the user provisioning request.
